quest_title: If the position vectors of a triangle's vertices are \(\vec{a}\), \(\vec{b}\) and \(\vec{c}\) then its area is:
explanation_txt:
With reference to figure,

\(\vec{d} = \vec{c} - \vec{a} \\ \vec{e} = \vec{b} - \vec{a} \)

\(\vec{d} \times \vec{e} = (\vec{c} - \vec{a}) \times (\vec{b} - \vec{a}) \\ 2 (Area) = (\vec{c} \times \vec{b} + \vec{a} \times \vec{c} + \vec{b} \times \vec{a} ) \)

Taking magnitude gives the answer as (a).

Length of seconds hand in a watch is 1 cm. the change in its velocity in 15 second is
explanation_txt:
\(\begin{array}{l}{\text { In } 15 \text { sec }} \\ {\theta=\cfrac{2 \pi}{60} \times 15=\cfrac{\pi}{2}} \\ {\omega=\cfrac{2 \pi}{60}=\cfrac{\pi}{30} \mathrm{rad} / \mathrm{s}}\end{array}\)

\(\begin{aligned} \text { Change in velocity } &=\sqrt{v_{2}^{2}+v_{1}^{2}} \\ &=\sqrt{(\mathrm{r} \omega)^{2}+(\mathrm{r} \omega)^{2}} \\ &=\sqrt{2 \mathrm{r}^{2} \omega^{2}}=\sqrt{2} \mathrm{r} \omega \\ &=\sqrt{2} \times 1 \times \cfrac{\pi}{30} \\ &=\cfrac{\pi}{30} \times \sqrt{2} \mathrm{cm} / \mathrm{s} \end{aligned}\)
